*Title*: VMWare Support Consultant

*Location*: Northern NJ

*Duration*: 6+ Months

*Position Description / Responsibilities*

Virtualize the physical servers to be on the VMWare platform.

Provide the WebSphere administration and support.

Provide the Domino, SQL server and .NET support.

Infrastructure support of the current Portal applications including the
installation, configuration, architecture, periodic monitoring, diagnosing,
troubleshooting and support of Portal servers.  Servers consist of IIS Web
servers, Verity (Autonomy) Search servers, .NET servers, SQL servers,
Notes/Domino servers, Web Trends servers and load balancing servers. Portal
servers consist of IIS/ADAM server, IBM WebSphere Portal servers, .NET
servers and SQL servers.

Coordinate with the Data Center Team on the overall infrastructure setup and
troubleshooting including servers, IP/DNS, SAN/backup, SQL connection, .NET
services, Windows/Domino Notes/other software upgrade, HP open view probes
setup, network tracing and periodic password change process of AD accounts
in SQL server, ADAM, .NET, WebSphere.

Maintain a list of passwords for all accounts of servers.

Work with the application teams to support the infrastructure needs
including documenting the server hardware/software build details,
recommending/documenting network topology architecture diagrams, resolving
the connectivity issues and hardware/software issues.

Communicate with the application team on the security patch updates.

Maintain the development servers (in the LAB) in a healthy state. Coordinate
with Data Center Team to maintain the production servers in a healthy state.

Rack the servers, partition the servers and install the necessary software
to get the server up and running in the Lab.

Participate in the Portal deployment activities, Windows 2003 SP1 upgrade
and VMWare migration activities.

*Required Skills:*

* *

*VMWare experience and skills *

Solid infrastructure experience in server builds, hardware partitioning /
software installation, troubleshooting any server/connection issues.

Solid experience and knowledge in Windows OS, TCP/IP, DNS, network routing /
tracing, VMWare, IIS, LDAP (ADAM), SQL Server and .NET servers.

Decent knowledge in IBM WebSphere Portal.

Knowledge of database design and cluster setup in SQL Server.

Knowledge in Domino.

*Preferred Skills:*

Understanding architectural modeling concepts with UML or Microsoft Visio,
Microsoft Project Plan.

Search experience in Autonomy is a plus

Strong understanding of all phases of the Software Development Life Cycle
and process methodologies using RUP - highly desired.

Any OS / Network / VMWare / WebSphere certification

